# 🚀 Page Based on CSS Float – Layout & Positioning

## 📌 Overview

This project represents my **third CSS project**, focusing on **Float and Positioning techniques**.

It is a static webpage where I practiced:

- Floating elements to create layouts  
- Using `position: sticky` and `position: fixed`  
- Controlling element placement and behavior on scroll  

🔗 **Live Demo:**  
https://abdelrahmangalal200101-cpu.github.io/Page-Based-On-Folat-Css/

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5  
- CSS3  
- CSS Float  
- CSS Positioning (sticky, fixed)  
- Responsive layout principles  

---

## 🎯 What I Learned

- How to use Float for layout design  
- Difference between static, relative, absolute, sticky, and fixed positioning  
- Creating sticky headers and fixed sidebars  
- Combining positioning with other CSS techniques for better layouts  
- Improving page structure and readability  

---

## 📈 Progress Note

This project shows my growth in **layout control and element positioning**, moving beyond Flexbox and Grid.

It prepared me for more advanced UI structures, and laid the groundwork for building component-based layouts in React and other frameworks.
